The screenplay is kinda bad but Jeremy Allen White and Zac Efron are insane in this.
sorry to be controversial but The Terminator is simply better than T2. Still some great action sequences in this but evil Schwarzenegger just hits different.
Julia Garner is an utter vision. The fact she's not in every film ever is a travesty of colossal proportions.

Kitty Green is a master at tension-building. Essentially a bottle thriller where you're just waiting... and waiting for the other shoe to drop, until it's not just the shoe, but the whole fuckin building that comes down with it. Having spent time passing through seedy bars in mining towns, I knew all these characters well. So glad Green has moved into features - she has such a unique vision that translates so well to the silver screen.
